# 00-baseline — AI-PR-Review baseline (always loaded)

This repo follows the AI-PR-Review baseline. Before proposing or applying any
change, read these files in order:

1. [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) — authoritative guidance, baseline section
   wrapped in `<!-- BEGIN BASELINE --> ... <!-- END BASELINE -->` markers.
2. [pr-rules/common.md](mdc:pr-rules/common.md) — cross-stack rules
   (security, secrets, scope, `[AI-Assisted]` PR tag, copyright).
3. [pr-rules/python.md](mdc:pr-rules/python.md) — Python rules.
4. [pr-rules/python.local.md](mdc:pr-rules/python.local.md) — repo-local
   Python overrides.
5. [pr-rules/service-html2md.md](mdc:pr-rules/service-html2md.md) —
   service-specific rules (CLI/runtime, log-export contract,
   Windows CI, symlinked CLAUDE.md).

## Hard rules — non-negotiable

- Never push, open, merge, or close PRs.
- Never read or write `.env*`, `*.pem`, `*.key`, `credentials.json`,
  `*.crt`, `id_rsa*`, `id_ed25519*`, `id_ecdsa*`, `id_dsa*`, or any file matching a sensible secret naming
  convention (e.g., `secrets.*`, `secret.*`, `*.secret.*`, `*.secrets.*`,
  `*api-token*`, `*-credentials.*`). See
  [pr-rules/common.md](mdc:pr-rules/common.md) §3 for the canonical list.
- Every AI-assisted PR title must start with `[AI-Assisted]` and the body
  must include the originating Claude / agent chat URL.
- Append edge cases to [pr-rules/edge-cases.md](mdc:pr-rules/edge-cases.md);
  never delete existing rows.

## Before every PR

Run `scripts/check_agents_consistency.sh` from the repo root. If it fails,
fix the baseline rather than weaken the script.
